# ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
# ║  Russell — Environment Configuration (.env.example)            ║
# ║                                                                ║
# ║  Copy to .env and fill in your values:                         ║
# ║    cp .env.example .env                                        ║
# ║                                                                ║
# ║  Or place at: ~/.config/harness/russell.env                    ║
# ║                                                                ║
# ║  Process env vars always override file values.                 ║
# ║  Discovery order: $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/harness/russell.env         ║
# ║                   → <repo_root>/.env → ./.env                  ║
# ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECTION 1: Russell Core (local, no API key required)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Tracing filter level: trace, debug, info, warn, error
# RUSSELL_LOG=info

# Global dry-run mode — set to 1 to prevent all mutations
# RUSSELL_DRY_RUN=0


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECTION 2: Russell Doctor — LLM backend (Okapi/Ollama)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Backend selection: okapi (default), ollama (alias for okapi), mock, offline
# RUSSELL_DOCTOR_BACKEND=okapi

# Model name — whatever is loaded in Okapi/Ollama
RUSSELL_DOCTOR_MODEL=nemotron-3-super:cloud

# Base URL for the LLM API (Okapi default)
# RUSSELL_DOCTOR_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:11435/v1

# API key for the LLM backend (not required for local Okapi)
# RUSSELL_DOCTOR_API_KEY=

# Minimum severity that triggers LLM escalation: crit, alert (default), warn, always
# RUSSELL_ESCALATE_MIN=alert

# OpenRouter API key — opt-in cloud LLM routing (see ADR-0016)
# Get one at: https://openrouter.ai/keys
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-...


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECTION 3: Kask MCP — bearer token for tool-call surface
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The Kask MCP surface exposes tools (search, memory, etc.) over
# JSON-RPC on localhost. Russell authenticates with a bearer token.
#
# HOW TO GET YOUR TOKEN:
#   Run on the Kask host:
#     stack-admin key set russell_mcp --for russell
#   This prints the token. Paste it below.
#
#   If you don't run Kask, leave these commented out — Russell
#   operates fine without MCP (degraded: no remote tool calls).

# Endpoint: must be loopback (enforced at connect time)
KASK_MCP_ENDPOINT=http://127.0.0.1:18100

# Bearer token — provision via stack-admin (see above)
# KASK_MCP_TOKEN=

# Tool list cache TTL in seconds (default: 300 = 5 min)
# KASK_MCP_TOOL_TTL_SECS=300

# HTTP request timeout in seconds (default: 30)
# KASK_MCP_TIMEOUT_SECS=30


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECTION 4: Brave Search API (optional — enables `workshop search --remote`)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Without this key, `russell workshop search` uses local cache only.
#
# HOW TO GET YOUR KEY:
#   1. Go to https://brave.com/search/api/
#   2. Click "Get Started" → sign up / sign in
#   3. Choose the "Free" tier (2,000 queries/month) or a paid plan
#   4. Copy the API key from the dashboard
#   5. Paste below (the key looks like: BSA...)
#
# BRAVE_API_KEY=


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECTION 5: Hugging Face (optional — for agent tooling / model access)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOT used by Russell's Rust code directly. This variable is consumed
# by external agent tooling (Kilo, MCP servers, etc.) that shares
# this .env file. If you only run Russell, you can skip this.
#
# WHICH VARIABLE TO USE:
#   The Hugging Face ecosystem recognizes HF_TOKEN as the canonical
#   variable (used by transformers, huggingface_hub, inference API).
#   However, some MCP servers and tools expect HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY.
#   Set both if unsure — they use the same token value.
#
# HOW TO GET YOUR TOKEN:
#   1. Go to https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
#   2. Click "New token"
#   3. Name it (e.g., "russell-workstation")
#   4. Choose scope:
#      - "Read" — sufficient for inference API and model downloads
#      - "Write" — needed only if pushing models/datasets
#   5. Copy the token (starts with hf_...)
#
# HF_TOKEN=hf_...
# HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY=hf_...


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECTION 6: Okapi / Ollama host (optional — for probes and scenarios)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Override the Okapi/Ollama host for health probes
# OLLAMA_HOST=127.0.0.1:11435

# Okapi binary and library paths (for okapi-watcher skill)
# OKAPI_BIN=$HOME/.local/bin/okapi
# OKAPI_LIB_DIR=$HOME/.local/lib/ollama


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECTION 7: Other agent/tool keys (not read by Russell directly)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These are consumed by MCP servers, Kilo agents, or other tooling
# that shares this .env file. Include them here for convenience.

# Firecrawl — web scraping service
# Get one at: https://www.firecrawl.dev/ → Dashboard → API Keys
# FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=fc-...

# Browserbase — cloud browser automation
# Get one at: https://www.browserbase.com/ → Settings → API Keys
# BROWSERBASE_API_KEY=bb_live_...
# BROWSERBASE_PROJECT_ID=
